Objectives / Learning Outcome(s) / Major:
THE STUDENT WILL BE ABLE TO:
1.DETERMINE THE PROPER METHOD OF ACCOUNTING FOR INVESTMENTS;
2.USE SUBSIDIARY LEDGERS TO ACCOUNT FOR RECEIVABLES
3.COMPUTE BAD DEBT EXPENSE USING THE ALLOWANCE METHOD
4.COMPUTE AND JOURNALIZE INTEREST BEARING NOTES RECEIVABLE;
5.EXPLAIN HOW THE USE OF CREDIT CARDS AND DISCOUNTED NOTES ARE USED TO ACCELERATE THE INFLOW OF CASH;
6.COMPUTE THE VALUE OF FIXED AND INTANGIBLE ASSETS;
7.DESCRIBE THE BALANCE SHEET PRESENTATION OF FIXED AND INTANGIBLE ASSETS;
8.COMPUTE DEPRECIATION AND AMORTIZATION METHODS UNDER FASB AND THE IRC RULES;
9.EXPLAIN INTERNAL CONTROL OF ASSETS;
10.IDENTIFY THE COMPONENTS OF CURRENT LIABILITIES AND THERE BALANCE SHEET PRESENTATION;
11.DETERMINE HOW AND WHEN TO ACCOUNT FOR CONTINGENT LIABILITIES;
12.SOLVE TIME VALUE OF MONEY PROBLEMS;
13.ILLUSTRATE THE ACCOUNTING FOR LONG-TERM LIABILITIES INCLUDING BONDS, AND CAPITAL LEASES;
14.COMPARE AND CONTRACT THE EQUITY SECTION OF CORPORATIONS, PROPRIETORSHIPS AND PARTNERSHIPS;
15.DISCUSS THE TYPES OF STOCK OWNERSHIP, AND THE RIGHTS OF STOCKHOLDERS;
16.ILLUSTRATE THE ACCOUNTING FOR CAPITAL STOCK ISSUANCE AND REPURCHASE;
17.PRODUCE A BALANCE SHEET CONTAINING TWO MAJOR SECTIONS OF STOCKHOLDERS EQUITY;
18.ILLUSTRATE THE ACCOUNTING FOR CHANGES IN THE APPROPRIATED AND UNAPPROPRIATED RETAINED EARNINGS ACCOUNTS;
19.EXPLAIN THE EFFECTS OF CASH DIVIDENDS, STOCK DIVIDENDS AND STOCK SPLITS ON STOCKHOLDERS EQUITY;
20.COMPUTE CORPORATE INCOME TAXES AND EXPLAIN TIMING DIFFERENCE BETWEEN TAX RECORDS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS;
21.COMPUTE EARNINGS PER SHARE;
22.COMPUTE EQUITY PER SHARE;
23.EXPLAIN COMPREHENSIVE INCOME;
24.CONSTRUCT A STATEMENT OF CASH FLOWS USING BOTH DIRECT AND INDIRECT METHODS; AND
25.ANALYZE CORPORATE ANNUAL REPORTS USING ANALYTICAL PROCEDURES TO ASSESS SOLVENCY AND PROFITABILITY.
